{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01TJHoTjnxpL95czLAPZQojr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now I know:\n- `mongodb-replica-0` is the PRIMARY\n- `mongodb-replica-1` and `mongodb-replica-2` are SECONDARIES\n\nThe plan:\n1. Update the ConfigMap with verbosity=2, slowOpThresholdMs=400, journalCompressor=zlib\n2. Rolling restart: restart secondaries first (replica-1, replica-2), then step down primary and restart replica-0\n3. Wait for each pod to be ready before proceeding\n\nFor the rolling restart strategy to maintain availability:\n1. Delete/restart mongodb-replica-1 (secondary) and wait for it to be ready\n2. Delete/restart mongodb-replica-2 (secondary) and wait for it to be ready\n3. Step down the primary (mongodb-replica-0) to trigger a new election, then delete/restart it and wait for it to be ready\n\nI could use `kubectl rollout restart` for the StatefulSet, but I need to check the updateStrategy first. The default for StatefulSets is RollingUpdate, which typically restarts pods from the highest ordinal downward.\n\nWith the default rolling update, it would restart mongodb-replica-2, then mongodb-replica-1, then mongodb-replica-0 (the primary). When the primary restarts, one of the already-updated secondaries will be elected as the new primary, maintaining availability throughout the process. The rolling update waits for each pod to be ready before moving to the next, which is exactly what we need here.\n\nThe readiness probe gives pods up to 90 seconds to become ready (30 second initial delay plus 6 failures at 10 second intervals), while the liveness probe allows 60 seconds for startup before killing the pod. So I'll update the ConfigMap and then trigger the rollout restart, waiting for it to complete.\n\nFor the WiredTiger journalCompressor change from zlib to zlib, since both the ConfigMap and pods were created around the same time with zlib already configured, the data is already using that compression format.\n\nI should focus on updating the verbosity and slowOpThresholdMs settings in the ConfigMap instead, then do a rolling restart to apply these changes. I'm considering whether to apply runtime parameter changes first without restarting to minimize downtime, but since the config file needs to be re-read anyway, a restart is necessary.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4521,"cache_read_input_tokens":31601,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4521},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4c245fca-9287-41a8-a409-17534c5ae788","uuid":"c1a687f8-14b7-4da3-b6f5-f13b6f08fecf","request_id":"req_011CcMXpJ8UpFwNbAJkduNid"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01TJHoTjnxpL95czLAPZQojr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good. `mongodb-replica-0` is PRIMARY, 1 and 2 are secondaries. The plan: update the ConfigMap (verbosity 1→2, slowOpThresholdMs 200→400, keep journalCompressor=zlib), then do a rolling restart (secondaries first, then primary) to apply consistently.\n\n**Step 1: Update the ConfigMap**"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4521,"cache_read_input_tokens":31601,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4521},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4c245fca-9287-41a8-a409-17534c5ae788","uuid":"c5b917d9-3dda-4640-a08a-b19632fd36b1","request_id":"req_011CcMXpJ8UpFwNbAJkduNid"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01TJHoTjnxpL95czLAPZQojr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0134EBmmBCchsfPoAcCsMbJE","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"export KUBECONFIG=/mydata/karma/runs/examples-rerererun/mongodb-mongod-config-update-20260624_052410/bundle/kubeconfig\n\nkubectl patch configmap mongod-config -n mongodb --type=merge -p '{\n  \"data\": {\n    \"mongod.conf\": \"storage:\\n  dbPath: /data/db\\n  wiredTiger:\\n    engineConfig:\\n      journalCompressor: zlib\\nnet:\\n  bindIpAll: true\\nreplication:\\n  replSetName: mongodb-replica\\nsecurity:\\n  authorization: enabled\\n  keyFile: /etc/mongo-keyfile/keyfile\\nsystemLog:\\n  verbosity: 2\\noperationProfiling:\\n  mode: slowOp\\n  slowOpThresholdMs: 400\\n\"\n  }\n}' 2>&1","description":"Patch ConfigMap with updated verbosity and slow-op threshold"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4521,"cache_read_input_tokens":31601,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4521},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4c245fca-9287-41a8-a409-17534c5ae788","uuid":"f3cdf344-5b8d-49eb-94b6-738a1c681005","request_id":"req_011CcMXpJ8UpFwNbAJkduNid"}
